{
  "texts": [
    "The shared use of EHRs for conflicting purposes exacerbates these ethical concerns.",
    "It's crucial to ensure that patient data is used to improve care, not merely to reduce costs.",
    "The differing applications of AI by hospitals and insurers could result in inconsistent care delivery-hospitals might leverage AI to justify necessary treatments, while insurers use it to minimize expenditures.",
    "To maintain trust and accountability, there must be transparency in how data and models are used by different entities.",
    "Regulatory bodies should oversee the deployment of LLMs to ensure fair and unbiased application."
  ]
}